{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/blog/top-apps-for-concentration/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Oganisyan Vrezh"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"d73b29b1-28e0-5706-b255-8893138f57a1","excerpt":"Nowadays, when consuming information is so easy, it‚Äôs become almost impossible to keep yourself concentrated even an hour without being distracted. Being able‚Ä¶","html":"<p>Nowadays, when consuming information is so easy, it‚Äôs become almost impossible to keep yourself concentrated even an hour without being distracted. Being able to work in a focus mode is the primary goal of every person who wants to be productive and avoid attacks of anxiety.</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 590px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/6dfce6952d27d3284e735bf9f4c2c972/97a96/preview.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 45.94594594594595%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"The Flow Mode\"\n        title=\"The Flow Mode\"\n        src=\"/static/6dfce6952d27d3284e735bf9f4c2c972/fcda8/preview.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/6dfce6952d27d3284e735bf9f4c2c972/12f09/preview.png 148w,\n/static/6dfce6952d27d3284e735bf9f4c2c972/e4a3f/preview.png 295w,\n/static/6dfce6952d27d3284e735bf9f4c2c972/fcda8/preview.png 590w,\n/static/6dfce6952d27d3284e735bf9f4c2c972/efc66/preview.png 885w,\n/static/6dfce6952d27d3284e735bf9f4c2c972/c83ae/preview.png 1180w,\n/static/6dfce6952d27d3284e735bf9f4c2c972/97a96/preview.png 2400w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">The Flow Mode</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<h2 id=\"table-of-contents\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#table-of-contents\" aria-label=\"table of contents permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Table of contents</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Part 1. <a href=\"#part-1-the-flow-mode\">The Flow Mode</a></li>\n<li>Part 2. <a href=\"#part-2-applications\">Applications</a></li>\n<li>Part 3. <a href=\"#part-3-notifications\">Notifications</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#literature\">Literature</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"part-1-the-flow-mode\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#part-1-the-flow-mode\" aria-label=\"part 1 the flow mode permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Part 1. The flow mode</h2>\n<p>The flow mode (or focused mode, or deep work) is the mental state in which a person performing an activity is fully immersed in a feeling of energized focus, full involvement, and enjoyment in the process of the activity <sup><a href=\"#literature\">1</a></sup>. </p>\n<p>‚ÑπÔ∏è You can find additional information about the concept in the <a href=\"#literature\">literature</a> section.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>‚ÄúThe best moments in our lives are not the passive, receptive, relaxing times‚Ä¶ The best moments usually occur if a person‚Äôs body or mind is stretched to its limits in a voluntary effort to accomplish something difficult and worthwhile.‚Äù ~ Mihaly Csikszentmihalyi</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>For now, let‚Äôs talk about different tools that may help you to keep this flow mode.</p>\n<h2 id=\"part-2-applications\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#part-2-applications\" aria-label=\"part 2 applications permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Part 2. Applications</h2>\n<p>In this part, I‚Äôd like to share applications that helped me to keep focused mode on by taking the ‚Äúmassive attack‚Äù of distractions.</p>\n<p>‚ÑπÔ∏è Note, you don‚Äô t need to use all mentioned applications together, just choose the ones that fit for you. However, I highly recommend giving a chance to all of them. After some time you‚Äôll start to see their positive influence.</p>\n<h3 id=\"pocket\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#pocket\" aria-label=\"pocket permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Pocket</h3>\n<p>‚ùóÔ∏èAvailability - <a href=\"https://getpocket.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Web</a> / <a href=\"https://apps.apple.com/us/app/pocket-save-read-grow/id309601447\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">iOS</a> / <a href=\"https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.ideashower.readitlater.pro\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Android</a> / <a href=\"https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/save-to-pocket/niloccemoadcdkdjlinkgdfekeahmflj?hl=en\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Browser Extension</a></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Pocket allows you to save the information and read it later. When you find something you want to view later, put it in Pocket.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><img src=\"https://i.pinimg.com/originals/6e/06/05/6e06055fd7702f8e9b458b296087f475.png\" alt=\"pocket-app-image\"></p>\n<p>So now you won‚Äôt be jumping forth and back every time you see an article worth reading. Just save to pocket (one click) without fears that you might miss important stuff.</p>\n<h3 id=\"the-20-second-rule\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#the-20-second-rule\" aria-label=\"the 20 second rule permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>The 20-second rule</h3>\n<p>‚ùóÔ∏èAvailability - <a href=\"https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/the-20-second-rule/mlonnhlhamjoopabmomhbdlddiomojpp?hl=en\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Browser Extension</a></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Application that enables you to make distracting sites 20 seconds harder to reach by showing you loader üîÑ</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>This extension will give you 20 seconds gap to fully realize whether you want to continue browsing to the site or not. You will have to just add distracting apps to the list.</p>\n<h3 id=\"blank-page\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#blank-page\" aria-label=\"blank page permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Blank page</h3>\n<p>‚ùóÔ∏èAvailability - <a href=\"https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/empty-new-tab-page/dpjamkmjmigaoobjbekmfgabipmfilij\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Browser Extension</a></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>With this extension, new tabs display a blank page instead of the usual new tab page with thumbnails</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>‚ÄúBlank Page‚Äù will help you to avoid opening ‚Äúanother important social network‚Äù every time you see it on your favorites list cause now you can see only a blank page.</p>\n<h3 id=\"tabsets\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#tabsets\" aria-label=\"tabsets permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Tabsets</h3>\n<p>‚ùóÔ∏èAvailability - <a href=\"https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/tabsets/ifohmndbcefggppiblfofpbkmdfmeing?hl=en\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Browser Extension</a></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Stores sets of tabs for later viewing</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Tabsets helps you to avoid keeping tons of different tabs at the same time by saving them into structured named folders.</p>\n<h3 id=\"haze-over\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#haze-over\" aria-label=\"haze over permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Haze Over</h3>\n<p>‚ùóÔ∏èAvailability - <a href=\"https://hazeover.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">MacOS</a></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>This app automatically highlights the front window by fading out all the background windows</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Haze Over will give you an opportunity to focus on the one tab so your attention won‚Äôt be taken away.</p>\n<h2 id=\"part-3-notifications\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#part-3-notifications\" aria-label=\"part 3 notifications permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Part 3. Notifications</h2>\n<blockquote>\n<p>If you want to remember just one thing from this article, then here it is: ‚ÄúMute all (no, I‚Äôm not kidding, ALL) notifications‚Äù.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I have dedicated an independent chapter for the ‚ÄúNotifications‚Äù to make clear its importance.</p>\n<p>From my point of view, the role of notifications is underestimated. They are unnoticeable but very dangerous so I recommend to start following them and you‚Äôll understand how often they are distracting from important tasks. My advice is turning them off (in case of messengers, mute almost all chats).</p>\n<p>üö´ If you have a fear of missing out, I‚Äôd recommend to create routine tasks to check notifications every couple of hours in a bunch. You‚Äôll be notified about everything without moving attention to the phone every time some shitty advertisers consider you as their target.</p>\n<p>Thanks for attention, be healthy and focused.</p>\n<h2 id=\"literature\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#literature\" aria-label=\"literature permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Literature</h2>\n<ol>\n<li><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Flow_(psychology)\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">The flow mode - Wikipedia</a></li>\n<li>‚ÄúFlow: The Psychology of Optimal Experience‚Äù ‚Äî Mihalyi Czikszentmihalyi</li>\n<li>‚ÄúDeep Work: Rules for Focused Success in a Distracted World‚Äù ‚Äî Cal Newport</li>\n<li>‚Äú–ü—É—Ç—å –î–∂–µ–¥–∞—è‚Äù ‚Äî –ú–∞–∫—Å–∏–º –î–æ—Ä–æ—Ñ–µ–µ–≤</li>\n</ol>","timeToRead":4,"frontmatter":{"title":"The Flow Mode","featuredImage":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":2.1739130434782608,"src":"/static/6dfce6952d27d3284e735bf9f4c2c972/ee604/preview.png","srcSet":"/static/6dfce6952d27d3284e735bf9f4c2c972/69585/preview.png 200w,\n/static/6dfce6952d27d3284e735bf9f4c2c972/497c6/preview.png 400w,\n/static/6dfce6952d27d3284e735bf9f4c2c972/ee604/preview.png 800w,\n/static/6dfce6952d27d3284e735bf9f4c2c972/f3583/preview.png 1200w,\n/static/6dfce6952d27d3284e735bf9f4c2c972/5707d/preview.png 1600w,\n/static/6dfce6952d27d3284e735bf9f4c2c972/0ef64/preview.png 2400w","sizes":"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px"}}},"date":"June 06, 2020","description":"About flow mode and the tools which may help you to keep this mode on!"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/top-apps-for-concentration/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/the-rule-of-20-links/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"The Rule of 20 Links üîó"},"fileAbsolutePath":"/Users/Vrezh/projects/oganisyan.com/content/blog/the-rule-of-20-links/index.md"},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/alice-in-it/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Alice in <del>Wonderland</del> IT"},"fileAbsolutePath":"/Users/Vrezh/projects/oganisyan.com/content/blog/alice-in-it/index.md"}}}}